---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Governance" description="Corporate & administrative setup">
	<section class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
		<h2 class="text-dim border-l-2 border-accent pl-4 mb-8">Corporate setup</h2>

		<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 not-prose">
			<div class="space-y-6">
				<div>
					<h3 class="text-text text-sm mb-2">Entity</h3>
					<p class="text-dim">Truss Labs Inc.<br/>New York C-Corporation</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h3 class="text-text text-sm mb-2">Registration</h3>
					<p class="text-dim">Incorporated: April 17, 2026</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h3 class="text-text text-sm mb-2">Location</h3>
					<p class="text-dim">Brooklyn, NY</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="bg-white/5 p-8 border border-white/10 space-y-4">
				<h3 class="text-accent text-sm">How it operates</h3>
				<p class="text-dim text-xs leading-relaxed">
					Truss Labs is an R&D lab. I picked a NY C-Corp for clean legal separation and low overhead during the pre-revenue phase — not because it's optimal for fundraising later (it isn't always).
				</p>
				<p class="text-dim text-xs leading-relaxed">
					Corporate documents, DNS configs, and filings live in a private <code>ilteris-company</code> repo, separate from the engineering work in <code>truss-labs</code>.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="mt-16 pt-12 border-t border-white/5">
			<h3 class="text-text mb-4">Capital</h3>
			<p class="text-dim text-sm">
				Capital is personal for now; no outside investment yet.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
